The article strongly supports the candidacy of Professor Sarah Cleveland to serve on the International Court of Justice, which is the main judicial organ of the United Nations. The author highlights Cleveland's talent as a scholar and practitioner of international law, as well as her commitment to principles such as judicial independence, rigor, and humanity. The article emphasizes the importance of the Court's work in addressing pressing global challenges. Cleveland's experience as a professor, government adviser, and expert on multilateral bodies, along with her respect for the diversity of legal systems, is seen as valuable for the Court's work. The author calls on all UN Member States to vote for Cleveland's candidacy, as the Court is regarded as a critical institution for advancing peace worldwide.